                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Most scientists aren’t in the business of creating new words. Especially chemists and biologists, who stick to a vernacular centered on proteins, molecules and genomes.&lt;/p>&lt;p>But Anil Vasudevan isn’t your typical scientist, and neither are the people on his team within AbbVie’s discovery science group.&lt;/p>&lt;p>Not only did they coin a new term – degradomers – they continue to build on years of work in this area around how this approach to degrading proteins could potentially help patients with debilitating diseases like rare cancers, immunological conditions and even Parkinson’s and Alzheimer’s diseases.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_1>
                <block_2
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
